genresAdvancedInfo.name: marinera
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Marinera is a traditional dance and music genre from Peru, with roots in Spanish and indigenous cultures. The music features a fast-paced rhythm, played on guitar, caj√≥n, and other percussion instruments. The dance is characterized by its elegant, flowing movements, with couples performing intricate footwork and hand gestures. Marinera is often performed at festivals and celebrations throughout Peru and has become a symbol of national identity.
